1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,680
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:04,680
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:08,920
My name is Catherine and today we have a very romantic dialogue for you.
我是Catherine，今天我们为大家准备了一段非常浪漫的对话。

4
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:09,920
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:11,800
Today we are at a shop and we are buying jewelry.
今天我们在一家商店里，正在买珠宝。

6
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:16,360
So of course there are many different types of jewelry and stones.
所以当然有很多不同类型的珠宝和宝石。

7
00:00:16,360 --> 00:00:18,720
So we're going to take a look at all that great stuff.
我们来看看这些好东西。

8
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:26,800
Let's jump into our dialogue and see what's going on.
让我们进入对话，看看发生了什么。

9
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,200
Good afternoon sir.
下午好，先生。

10
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,400
Is there anything I can help you with today?
今天有什么可以帮您的吗？

11
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,400
Yeah.
嗯。

12
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,880
I'm looking for a nice gift to give my girlfriend.
我在找一份好礼物送给我女朋友。

13
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:36,240
Our fifth anniversary is next Friday.
下周五是我们五周年纪念日。

14
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:41,180
Well I would be happy to assist you in choosing the perfect gift for her.
我很乐意帮您为她挑选完美的礼物。

15
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:44,120
Is there anything in particular that you have in mind?
您心里有什么特别的想法吗？

16
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:46,080
No, not really.
没有，不太有。

17
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,480
I'm completely at a loss.
我完全没头绪。

18
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:55,560
Well you can give her a set of pearl earrings or this beautiful heart shaped pendant.
嗯，您可以送她一套珍珠耳环，或者这个漂亮的爱心形吊坠。

19
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:57,960
What is her favorite gemstone?
她最喜欢的宝石是什么？

20
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,960
That purple one.
那个紫色的。

21
00:00:58,960 --> 00:00:59,960
I'm sorry.
抱歉。

22
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,800
I've never bought jewelry for anyone and I'm kind of nervous.
我从没给任何人买过珠宝，有点紧张。

23
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:03,800
Don't worry.
别担心。

24
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:09,760
We specialize in providing our customers a relaxed, pressure free shopping environment.
我们专为顾客提供轻松、无压力的购物环境。

25
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,260
That stone is an amethyst.
那块石头是紫水晶。

26
00:01:12,260 --> 00:01:15,640
We have a range of beautiful amethyst pieces.
我们有一系列漂亮的紫水晶饰品。

27
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,600
Take a look at this bracelet.
看看这个手镯。

28
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:22,900
It's 18 karat rose gold studded with amethyst and blue topaz.
它是18K玫瑰金，镶嵌紫水晶和蓝托帕石。

29
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:25,200
It's a great statement piece.
这是一件很抢眼的饰品。

30
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,280
Oh wow.
哦，哇。

31
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,640
That's really pretty.
真漂亮。

32
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:30,560
Jess would love that.
Jess会喜欢的。

33
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:33,640
But I was thinking of something a little more delicate.
但我想要更精致一点的东西。

34
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,680
Perhaps a necklace?
也许是一条项链？

35
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:41,160
We have this beautiful platinum pendant or you could also get her a locket.
我们有这条漂亮的铂金吊坠，或者您也可以给她买个盒式项链坠。

36
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:43,320
You could also get her a timepiece.
您也可以给她买一块手表。

37
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:46,240
It's both glamorous and functional.
它既迷人又实用。

38
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:50,680
If you tell me a little more about your girlfriend, maybe I can help you find something for her.
如果您多告诉我一些关于您女朋友的事，也许我能帮您找到适合她的东西。

39
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,680
Jess?
Jess？

40
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:53,280
Well, she's very smart.
嗯，她很聪明。

41
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,160
She has a great sense of humor.
她很有幽默感。

42
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,160
She's very feminine.
她很有女人味。

43
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:59,400
Perhaps you could give her a ring.
也许您可以送她一枚戒指。

44
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:04,120
Well, actually I was thinking about asking Jess to marry me.
嗯，其实我在想向Jess求婚。

45
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:06,000
I've just been so nervous.
我一直很紧张。

46
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,160
Well, sir, I believe your fifth anniversary is a great time to propose.
嗯，先生，我觉得五周年纪念日是求婚的好时机。

47
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:13,000
Okay, I've decided.
好，我决定了。

48
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,200
I'm going to pop the question.
我要求婚了。

49
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,320
Fabulous.
太棒了。

50
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:18,880
We should look at engagement rings then.
那我们该看看订婚戒指了。

51
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:21,840
Now that's a whole other section.
那完全是另一个区域了。

52
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:25,800
All right.
好的。

53
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,800
We're back.
我们回来了。

54
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:30,240
Let's take a look at Language Takeaway.
让我们看看“语言要点”部分。

55
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:33,040
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

56
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:38,920
In Language Takeaway, we have a lot of jewelry words and terms for you.
在“语言要点”中，我们为您准备了很多珠宝词汇和术语。

57
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,560
So let's take a look at some of these.
所以让我们来看看其中的一些。

58
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:44,080
The first one I want to talk about, Marco, is pearl earrings.
Marco，我想谈的第一个是珍珠耳环。

59
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,080
That's right.
没错。

60
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:49,360
The sales assistant offered a set of pearl earrings.
销售助理推荐了一套珍珠耳环。

61
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:52,240
So we have earrings that you wear on your ears, right?
所以耳环是戴在耳朵上的，对吧？

62
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,240
Usually girls.
通常是女生戴。

63
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,240
Yes.
是的。

64
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,600
But what about pearl?
那珍珠呢？

65
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:59,320
Pearls are a kind of decoration that come from inside an animal.
珍珠是一种来自动物体内的装饰品。

66
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:05,160
The clam is a sea animal that opens up and inside there might be a little pearl.
蛤蜊是一种海洋动物，它张开后里面可能有一颗小珍珠。

67
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:09,600
It's usually a white or pink, very, very pretty object.
它通常是白色或粉色的，非常非常漂亮的东西。

68
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,760
And we sometimes put them in earrings or on a necklace.
我们有时把它们放在耳环或项链上。

69
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:13,760
That's right.
没错。

70
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:18,760
So a set of pearl earrings are earrings that have this little rock or this little marble
所以一套珍珠耳环就是耳环上有这种小石头或小珠子

71
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:21,240
looking thing on it.
一样的东西。

72
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:25,600
And well, he also offered a beautiful heart-shaped pendant.
嗯，他还推荐了一个漂亮的爱心形吊坠。

73
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,600
Okay.
好的。

74
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,200
A pendant is a kind of necklace.
吊坠是一种项链。

75
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:31,840
And basically a pendant is something that hangs down.
基本上，吊坠是垂下来的东西。

76
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:35,080
So in this case, it's a necklace that might have something on the bottom that hangs down
所以在这种情况下，它是一条项链，底部可能挂着东西

77
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:37,220
like in the shape of a heart.
比如心形。

78
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:39,200
So that's what heart-shaped means.
这就是爱心形的意思。

79
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:41,160
It means that it has the shape of a heart.
意思是它有心的形状。

80
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:44,800
Like for example, you can have a heart-shaped cake.
比如，你可以有一个心形蛋糕。

81
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,280
You can also have a heart-shaped face.
你也可以有颗心形脸。

82
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,280
Okay.
好的。

83
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,280
Very good.
非常好。

84
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:53,640
And of course the pendant is a little thing that hangs from the necklace.
当然，吊坠是挂在项链上的小东西。

85
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:58,800
Now maybe some pendants can also have a gemstone and that's our next word.
现在，有些吊坠可能还带有宝石，这就是我们下一个词。

86
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:02,400
So a gemstone is not just a normal stone.
所以，宝石不是普通的石头。

87
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:06,080
It's a beautiful, normally expensive stone.
它是一种漂亮、通常很昂贵的石头。

88
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:10,000
And we often have gemstones that relate to a person's birthday.
我们经常有与人的生日相关的宝石。

89
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Right.
对。

90
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Right.
对。

91
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,720
So these come in many different colors and types.
所以这些宝石有很多不同的颜色和种类。

92
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:19,240
The two that we heard about in today's dialogue are purple and blue.
我们今天对话中提到的两种是紫色和蓝色。

93
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,240
That's right.
没错。

94
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:25,120
The purple stone that you're talking about is the one that the shop assistant suggested,
你提到的紫色石头是店员建议的那种，

95
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,640
which is amethyst.
也就是紫水晶。

96
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,880
Amethyst is a purple stone.
紫水晶是一种紫色的石头。

97
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:33,000
It's really, really pretty and it's sometimes light, sometimes a little bit darker.
它非常非常漂亮，有时颜色浅，有时稍微深一点。

98
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,240
Depends on the one that you're looking at.
取决于你看到的那颗。

99
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:39,400
But amethyst is a little bit, it's a little bit difficult to say, but it's a kind of gemstone.
但紫水晶有点，有点难说，但它是一种宝石。

100
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,760
The other one we heard about is called topaz.
我们听到的另一种叫托帕石。

101
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,760
Okay.
好的。

102
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:43,760
A topaz.
托帕石。

103
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,120
And this one is blue.
这个是蓝色的。

104
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:49,960
So I guess they all look very much like diamonds, but they are different colors.
所以我想它们看起来都很像钻石，但颜色不同。

105
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:52,280
So topaz looks like a blue diamond kind of.
所以托帕石看起来有点像蓝色钻石。

106
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:53,280
Right.
对。

107
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,280
And ruby is red.
红宝石是红色的。

108
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,600
And ruby is red.
红宝石是红色的。

109
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,600
Very good.
非常好。

110
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,600
I think there's a black one that's called onyx.
我想有一种黑色的叫缟玛瑙。

111
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,600
Onyx is black.
缟玛瑙是黑色的。

112
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,600
That's right.
没错。

113
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,600
Okay.
好的。

114
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,680
So many different types of gemstones.
所以有很多不同类型的宝石。

115
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:07,120
And as Catherine said, usually each month has a specific gemstone.
正如凯瑟琳所说，通常每个月都有特定的宝石。

116
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:10,160
So that's considered your gemstone if you were born on that month.
所以如果你出生在那个月，那就是你的生辰石。

117
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,160
Exactly.
正是。

118
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,160
All right.
好的。

119
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:17,440
